###### Prepare the data
### Drop some columns - the columns to drop are decided after looking at pearson correlations and p-values of linear regression

bb_train = bb_train.drop('honeybee', axis = 1)
bb_train = bb_train.drop('RainingDays', axis = 1)
bb_train = bb_train.drop('MaxOfLowerTRange', axis = 1)
bb_train = bb_train.drop('MinOfLowerTRange', axis = 1)
bb_train = bb_train.drop('AverageOfLowerTRange', axis = 1)


### Checked for nulls, there are none

### Create X and Y
Y = bb_train['yield']
X = bb_train.drop(['id','yield'], axis = 1)

### Normalize the data
std = StandardScaler()
X = std.fit_transform(X)
In [170]:
